Some of our favorite places in📍Naples, Florida:

Three60 Market- amazing wine prices and great breakfast food! They’re opening a tasting room soon across the street! 

Turtle Club- sadly it’s closed right now because of Ian, but re-opening this year. The best food & drinks. You can eat on the beach and watch the sun set and it’s gorgeous! 

Bay House- get the lychee martini if they have it! 

Bayside- Great for 4th of July to see fireworks. Their NYE meal options were so delicious and it’s kid friendly. 

Bricktops- my favorite restaurant probably ever. The espresso martinis are top notch but the prickly pear margarita is TO DIE FOR. The firecracker roll is beyond delicious. 

The Bevy- amazing drink selection and the vibe is impeccable! 

The London Club- dark and moody jazz bar vibes with live music and delicious food! 

Naples Surf Shop- awesome selection of clothing and shoes for men, women, and kids! 

Bicé- Amazing patio for cocktails as the sun sets. 

Port O Call Marina- the best boat rental experience! We rent the tritoon boat and go to Keewaydin Island for the day!

Seed To Table- the way they stack the fruits and veggies is unbelievable. 🤣 The produce looks fake it’s so pretty. You can grab a mimosa while you shop and they have restaurants, too! 

Drop your favorites in the comments! 

@thelondonclubnaples @oldnaplessurfshop @naplesbevy @thebayhouse @turtleclubnaples @portocallmarina @three60market

Make your grocery store flowers look designer with these tips! 

-Mix flowers with different textures. 
-Always grab one filler flower- puffy florals like hydrangeas take up a lot of space and you don’t need that many!
-Add in spillers like eucalyptus. The way these spill over the sides adds volume to your arrangement. 
-Add large leaves to the inside of your vase for a more modern look. I used aspidistra leaves from a local florist (they were only $3!) but you can also purchase waterproof ribbon that looks similar.

Say goodbye to this decorating disaster!  Elevate your living room with these Tips for Choosing the Right Coffee Table from @homedepot. #TheHomeDepotpartner 

1. Choose a size and shape that fits your living room layout and existing furniture. Ideally, the coffee table should be about two-thirds the length of your sofa and at a height that is level with or slightly lower than the seat cushions.
2. Think about functionality and storage options that fit your needs. 
3. Consider the style and design of the coffee table to match your living room’s aesthetic.

Our sweet sweet Dwayne passed away last night. Dwayne, Wayne, Wayne Wayne, Wayney, Insaney Delaney, Inaners Delaners, we miss you so much bubba. I know you’re snuggled up with my Dad in heaven and I just know he’s so happy to see you. Today we got the keys to our next fixer upper. Thank you to everyone who send kind and encouraging messages about Dwayne yesterday. We are still trying to process everything but trying to stay positive and cheerful for Jett. Spooky portrait Halloween DIY! This was so easy to make, here are the directions: 
- Source vintage frame (I got this one @goodwill)! 
- Take apart your frame to determine what size print you need. 
- Print a portrait from the public domain. The one I used is called “Girl With An Orchid” 
- Print your portrait. I got this one printed @staples on poster paper and the quality was great. 
- Trace and paint a mask onto the portrait. You can use acrylic paint. 
- For the sparkles I found adhesive backed rhinestones in the scrapbooking section at the craft store! 

Tag me in stories if you try this, I’d love to see what you create!
